<HEADLINE>
BATTING SLUMP IS OVER, IT'S MILLER'S TIME 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By DON KETCHUM  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ It was a picture of frustration, and it had  &UR; Damian
 &UR; Miller's face right smack dab in the middle.
</P>
<P>
   Entering Saturday night's game against the Atlanta Braves, the
catcher had struck out five times in as many at-bats and had one
measly walk.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think I have ever struck out that many times in a row
before,'' Miller said. ``I'm wearing a path between the plate and
the dugout walking back.''
</P>
<P>
   Miller was able to get a bit more exercise Saturday night,
legging out a pair of doubles to right field and hitting a single
to emerge from his slump in Arizona's 8-3 victory, its first of the
season. The Diamondbacks amassed 16 hits.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Kelly Stinnett continues to be hobbled by a bruised quadriceps
muscle suffered in Friday night's series opener.  &UR; Greg Colbrunn,
the third catcher, has been away from the team since midweek due to
the death of his grandmother. &QL; 
Wohlers a temptation &QL; 
Right-hander  &UR; Mark Wohlers a Diamondback?
</P>
<P>
   It's a remote possibility.
</P>
<P>
   The man who had 77 saves for the Atlanta Braves from 1995 to
1997, then ran into mechanical and personal problems, was
designated for assignment by the Braves on Friday.
</P>
<P>
   He must first clear waivers, and if that occurs by Monday, he
could agree to go to the minor leagues or elect to become a free
agent. &QL; 
Chouinard in, Young out &QL; 
The Diamondbacks, wanting to add an 11th pitcher to the roster with
right-hander  &UR; Armando Reynoso joining the rotation, purchased the
contract of right-hander  &UR; Bobby Chouinard from Triple-A Tucson and
designated outfielder  &UR; Ernie Young for assignment.
</P>
<P>
   Because he is out of options, Young will be placed on waivers
beginning Monday, and if he clears by Wednesday, the Diamondbacks
will re-sign him and send him to Tucson. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
