<P>
   FAA-Y2K (Denver) _ In a Y2K test of some of the most critical
computers in the country, the Federal Aviation Administration set
the clocks ahead to December 31, 1999, on Saturday night in Denver,
and let the system monitor thousands of flights as it rolled over
to Jan. 1, 2000. The agency spent the last few months preparing the
computers, but this was its major ``end-to-end'' test to see if
everything still works when it's all plugged together. A look at
how they did. By Matthew L. Wald.
