<P>
   KOSOVO-MAIN _ WASHINGTON _ NATO said Sunday that the air war
against Yugoslavia is expected to go on ``many more weeks.''
Meanwhile, key members of Congress, which is returning Monday after
its Easter recess, are urging President Clinton to begin planning
for the use of U.S. ground forces. Developing. (Shepard, Cox News
Service)
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-AIRBASE _ RINAS AIR FIELD, Albania _ In just seven days,
the United States Air Force has turned this sleepy Albanian airport
into a surging Western military airbase which is already moving in
more military supplies than during the Berlin Airlift. For the
airmen and women filling the sandbags and running the air tower,
the biggest headache is the mud. It's rained hard for the past
several nights, and people have up to six inches of water in their
tents when they wake up in the morning. Once the base is fully
operational, it will be one of the busiest air fields in the world.
(Kunstel/Albright, Cox News Service). With PHOTOS. 25.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-WITNESSES _ STANKOVAC, Macedonia _ The horrific stories
ethnic Albanians are bringing from Kosovo to refugee camps here
could make them witnesses for the prosecution in future war crimes
trials. Scores of Western investigators are interviewing the
refugees and are meticulously gathering eyewitness accounts. But
hard evidence is in short supply from some refugees, who say Serb
soldiers and militia wore masks to shield their identities.
(Holmes, Cox News Service) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   TOPMAYOR _ Clarence Anthony grew up in an impoverished farm
family in one of the nation's poorest towns, but that hasn't
stopped him from success. After toiling in the fields as a boy and
putting himself through college by working in a supermarket,
Anthony was elected mayor of tiny South Bay at the tender age of
24, becoming one of Florida's first African-American mayors.
Fifteen years later, he's still mayor, but much more: Anthony was
recently elected as president of the National League of Cities. We
profile the mayor, whose son happens to be Reidel Anthony, a star
receiver with the NFL Tampa Bay Buccaneers. (MWilliams, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED
</P>
