RANCH (Phoenix) Five former employees of Arizona Boys Ranch face a
crucial hurdle this week in their battle against charges that they
murdered a 16-year-old client at the home for delinquents in March
1998. The defendants will appear Tuesday in Pinal County Superior
Court for a preliminary hearing, where Judge Richard Fields is
expected to decide whether there is probable cause for a trial.
While most preliminary hearings are perfunctory events, defense
lawyers said they intend to use the forum as a three-day mini-trial
in this case. And it will be preceded with a hot dispute over
motions seeking to dismiss the charges entirely. By DENNIS WAGNER.
