<SLUG> BC-NY-MISSING-STUDENT-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
(ATTN: S.C.)  
 SOUTH CAROLINA COLLEGE STUDENT DISAPPEARS ON TRIP TO NEW YORK
</HEADLINE>
   (sw) 
 By MICHAEL COOPER   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A college student from South Carolina who came to New
York on a school trip disappeared after attending an advertising
symposium on Friday, the police said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   The student, Sarah Efird, 21, was last seen on Friday afternoon
leaving an office building in Times Square, said Sgt. Gerry Falcon,
a police spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Efird, a senior studying advertising at the University of
South Carolina in Columbia, won a trip to New York to meet
advertising executives, her mother, Frances Efird, said in a
telephone interview from Greenville, S.C.
</P>
<P>
   On Friday morning, Ms. Efird attended a symposium at Saatchi &AMP;
Saatchi, in Greenwich Village, Mrs. Efird said. She apparently left
behind her backpack containing her wallet, a jacket and her plane
tickets, her mother said.
</P>
<P>
   That afternoon, Mrs. Efird said, Ms. Efird accompanied a friend
to the offices of the cable network Nickelodeon at 1515 Broadway in
Times Square. The friend, who was not identified, had hoped to get
a job interview with Nickelodeon.
</P>
<P>
   But Ms. Efird left by herself. Mrs. Efird speculated that her
daughter may have left alone because a friend's birthday was on
Saturday and she wanted to surprise him with a gift. She was seen
on a surveillance camera leaving the building without a coat, her
mother said.
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Efird never rejoined her group at the Doral Hotel, and never
contacted two friends from South Carolina that she had planned to
spend the weekend with in New York, Mrs. Efird said.
</P>
<P>
   The police described Ms. Efird as 5 feet 4 inches tall, about
115 pounds, with medium-length brown hair and hazel eyes. They
urged anyone who may have seen her to call, toll-free, (800)
577-TIPS.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
